<Author>pippippooray
<Content>For the price there are better places, though location good. It was OK if the main thing was to have a cheap room in walking distance of the centre - its very near the reijksmuseum and the outer ring of the central canals, and the Vondelpark is lovely. Designer shops alll along the road if you like window shopping. And to be fair, the reception staff were nice and friendly and helpful. However, the hotel is dingy and shabby throughout, reception carpet worn through and very worn and faded bedroom furnishings. The lift was tiny and made worrying creaking noises, and our room was a few flights of stairs further up than the lift went, so not for the elderly or infirm. we had an en suite bathroom and the shower worked, but the bathroom was grubby and cracked. Our radiator didnt work, when on it gurgled loudly, when off the room was freezing and the bedding too thin to get warm. We asked for someone to bleed the radiator but there was no evidence of this having been done, and by the time we got back each night we were too tired to worry about it really. The beds were very low and the mattresses inadequate. I didnt see any evidence of mice, but both of us did get a load of bites on our legs which looked like fleabites and took ages to clear up. The breakfast was a standard continental style, plentiful (with a warning not to make sandwiches for your lunch on the wall!) and it was nice that it was included in the deal as often it isnt. definitely not ideal for a romantic weekend, but ok if youre backpacking with friends. though even then, Id say the youth hostel round the corner where I stayed last year was clean and cheap and cheerful if youre with friends, and if youre with your partner/family, I'm probably with the people recommending you try somewhere else... 
