<Author>cmw10
<Content>Pleasant Stay for the Price I stayed here for 2 nights in a 3-person room on the top floor. My first piece of advice: if you hate stairs, don't come here. The walk up to the first floor is almost a straight vertical, especially scary on the way down. Since our room was on the top floor we had two more stories to climb, which is a hike after a long day of walking. Ask for a room without the high windows, since we coudn't even see out of ours without climbing on a chair. The toilet in the hallway is small but clean, though I was a little disappointed by the shower, which was a little grimy (I brought shower shoes). The room itself was nice, and the beds were comfortable. The staff were very friendly and gave us advice on what to see in the city. I would say its best feature is its location, on a very chic shopping street and right next to all the major museums. If you're on a budget, this is a great place to stay. 
