<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Highly recommened for location and cheap price (50 euro double) The PC Hooft had a great location - right by Vondel park and a 5 minute walk from the Leidsplien.Its a one star hotel and there is not elevator and most of the rooms share a bathroom. This might seem like a problem for many Americans who are used to Ramada style accomodations but it is not bad at all.There were separate toilets for men and women and two shower rooms shared between 8 or so rooms on our floor. The bathrooms were clean and I never had to wait for the other guests during my five night stay. Each room had its own sink. The rooms were small but comfortable enough. I don't think the rooms were air conditioned but I am not sure as we were there in April it wasn't necessary.Breakfast is included - it is served until 11 am and included hard boiled eggs, ham  cheese, coffee, tea juice and rolls with jam.All in all my brother and I were very happy with the service and rooms at a cost of 50 Euro a night. 
