<Content>What a dive! This hotel was advertised in Time Out. No mention was made of the fact that you would need a Sherpa to guide you up the practically vertical stairs. Our double room was on the top floor so we had to climb about 45-50 steps up and down. The stench of smoke in the room was appalling. Burning incense and opening the window had no effect. Make sure you sleep with someone you get on with really well as you will be very close to them all night (due to the fact that the bed slopes down from either side into the middle). The breakfast was pretty average for the continent. The toilet was tiny, the paper provided was more smear than wipe. The shower was mouldy and uninviting. We went home tired, dirty and exhausted! The only good thing about it was the fact that it was pretty much within walking distance of the centre of town. All this for 65 euros a night. Try the Ibis instead! 
